title: Storm Doris soaks TV journalists across the country
text: Beleaguered TV journalists get soaked as they are dispatched to seafronts across Britain to report on Storm Doris BBC's Alison Freeman felt the full force of Storm Doris on Blackpool seafront Reporter desperately tried to talk about the storm while her sound cut out Viewers could just about make out her saying she had been there since 5am ITV stationed freezing reporters at waterfronts in Merseyside and Blackpool Viewers took to Twitter to question why the presenters were being 'tortured'
